message:
Swapped Logger and Category. Thus, instead of

  class Category implements AppenderAttachable {..}
  class Logger extends Category {}

we now have

  class Category extends Logger {}
  class Logger implements AppenderAttachable {..}

As Category extends Logger, users will still be able to use
it. However, doing so will generate a deprecation warning.


git-svn-id: https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/logging/log4j/trunk@310813 13f79535-47bb-0310-9956-ffa450edef68

The default constructor of an Appender
is intended to be used with log4j Configurators (through config files).

For programmatic oconfigration, the general and recommendded
usage pattern is:

XAppender xa = new XAppender();
xa.setThisOption(...);
xa.setThatOption(...);
xa.activateOptions();

All constructors in Appenders which create a directly usable appender
instances take parameters. None of them create a usable instance with
the default (no parameter) constructor.


